Package: betaMix
Type: Package
Title: Detect Edges in Co-Expression Graphs
Version: 0.3.2
Authors@R: person(given = "Haim",
                  family = "Bar",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "haim.bar@uconn.edu")
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.5), Matrix, methods, nleqslv
Suggests: knitr, markdown, rmarkdown, testthat (>= 3.0.0), DBI, RSQLite
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Description: Detects edges in co-expression networks by fitting a two-component beta
    mixture model to the pairwise correlation statistics of all predictor pairs
    simultaneously. Unlike regression-based approaches that require P separate model
    fits (one per variable as the response), betaMix fits a single model to all
    P(P-1)/2 pairs in one step. False positive control is provided by both a
    frequentist Type I error bound (maxalpha) and a Bayesian posterior probability
    threshold (ppr), enforced simultaneously.
